From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0043/N] buildjdk-spec: override OS defines to host-Linux for BUILD pass

Patches 0004/0037 force `-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -DBSD -D_GNU_SOURCE
-D_DEFAULT_SOURCE` into both `CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM` and
`CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JDK` for `OPENJDK_TARGET_OS=bsd`. The BUILDJDK pass
inherits the target's spec.gmk and these defines leak into the
host (x86 Linux) compile, which causes BSD-only includes like
`<net/if_dl.h>` (NetworkInterface.c), `<machine/endian.h>`
(fdlibm.h, fixed by 0042 via `__linux__` priority) and host glibc
identifier hiding to surface.

Patches 0040, 0042 fix several files by re-ordering `#ifdef`s to
prefer `__linux__` when both `_ALLBSD_SOURCE` and `__linux__` are
defined. But that approach scales linearly with each new file we
hit. Cleaner: override OS defines in `buildjdk-spec.gmk.in` so the
BUILD pass uses Linux-appropriate flags. The target spec on
CheriBSD is untouched.

Same shape as the existing `EXTRA_*FLAGS` overrides (patch 0013)
and the `SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE` override (patch 0038).

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0043)

--- a/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
+++ b/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
@@ -108,3 +108,9 @@
 # Strip the bsd-target --undefined-version LLD flag for the BUILD pass:
 # host GNU ld 2.38 doesn't recognize it (added in binutils 2.40).
 override SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE = -Wl,-version-script=$1
+
+# The BUILD pass runs on the host (Linux x86); the target's bsd OS-defines
+# (_ALLBSD_SOURCE, BSD) make host glibc hide identifiers and trigger BSD-only
+# #include paths. CFLAGS_JDKLIB etc. are baked at configure time as a single
+# string with the target's OS defines embedded; we can't fix this by overriding
+# CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JDK alone (CFLAGS_JDKLIB has the value already substituted).
+# Filter out the bsd defines from the BUILD-pass JDK CFLAGS post-include.
+override CFLAGS_JDKLIB   := $(filter-out -D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -DBSD,$(CFLAGS_JDKLIB)) -DLINUX
+override CFLAGS_JDKEXE   := $(filter-out -D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -DBSD,$(CFLAGS_JDKEXE)) -DLINUX
+override CXXFLAGS_JDKLIB := $(filter-out -D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -DBSD,$(CXXFLAGS_JDKLIB)) -DLINUX
+override CXXFLAGS_JDKEXE := $(filter-out -D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -DBSD,$(CXXFLAGS_JDKEXE)) -DLINUX
